'''Stratton Park Halt''' served the community of [[Stratton St Margaret]], now part of the [[Borough of Swindon]] in [[Wiltshire]], England. The station was on the main [[Great Western Railway]] [[Great Western Main Line|line]] from London to Bristol and opened around 1840.<ref>[http://www.wiltshire-opc.org.uk/Items/Stratton%20St.%20Margaret%20-%20Railway%20History.pdf]</ref> The Beeching cuts brought its closure in 1964, by which time it was only served by five trains per day.<ref name="SPL">[http://www.steampicturelibrary.com/en/stratton-park-halt/print/8748565.html]</ref>

